  "description": "Alleppey (Alappuzha) is the hub of Kerala's backwater tourism, offering a mesmerizing network of lagoons, canals, lakes, and rivers stretching over 900 km. A houseboat cruise through the palm-fringed waterways is one of India's most iconic travel experiences. The Punnamada Lake, Vembanad Lake, and the maze of narrow canals create a surreal landscape that's unlike anything else in the world. Alleppey is also famous for the Nehru Trophy Boat Race, one of the most spectacular boat races in India.",
